Company Description: 'warren Electric Cooperative Warren Electric Cooperative Was Incorporated IN May Of 1939 Through The Efforts Of Several Local Farmers And Businessmen Who Wanted To Bring Electricity To Warren County Rural Areas. The First Substation Was Energized IN 1940 At Pittsfield. The Original Office Was Located IN Pittsfield Until 1943 When The Office Was Moved To Youngsville, Pa. IN 1951 The Office Moved To Its Present Location At 320 East Main Street Youngsville. Today, Warren Electric Has Six Substations, Three Metering Points And Maintains 1, 050 Miles Of Line Serving 8, 851 Meters Throughout Warren, Forest, Venango, Crawford And Erie Counties. As A Member Of The Cooperative, You Have A Voice IN The Governing Of The Cooperative. Each Year On May 15th, The Members Of The Cooperative Vote At The Annual Meeting. They Elect Directors To Represent Their Interest. A Board Of Nine Directors, Elected From The General Membership, Set The Policies And Make The Decisions That Guide The Cooperative To Achieve The Best Results For The Members. IN Other Electric Utilities Such As First-Energy ( Formerly Penelec ), The Stockholder Elects The Board Of Directors, Who IN Turn Set The Policies. The Actual Consumer Has No Voice IN The Decisions Of The Utility. As A Cooperative Member, You Are Not Only The Consumer, But Also The Stockholder. Your Cooperative Office Remains Open And Continues To Be An Integral Part Of The Community. We Pledge Not Only To Deliver Electricity But To Try To Improve The Quality Of Life IN Rural Areas Whenever Possible. Warren Electric Has Already Helped Bring Dry Fire Hydrants To The Rural Townships, Offer Surge And Lightning Protection At Wholesale Cost To Our Members And We Are Working With Our Statewide Organization Prea & Allegheny Electric Cooperative To Bring An Affordable Alternative On-Lot Sewage Systems To Rural Areas. We Will Continue To Serve Our Members With Reliable Service, Reasonable Rates And Improved Quality Of Life IN Rural Areas. We Are People You Can Count On.'

Company Description: Cummins Sales And Service Is The Registered Trade Name Of Cummins Inc. IN North America. Cummins Inc., A Global Power Leader, Is A Corporation Of Complementary Business Units That Design, Manufacture, Distribute And Service Diesel And Natural Gas Engines And Related Technologies, Including Fuel Systems, Controls, Air Handling, Filtration, Emission Solutions And Electrical Power Generation Systems. Headquartered IN Columbus, Indiana, (Usa) Cummins Currently Employs Approximately 55,000 People Worldwide And Serves Customers IN Approximately 190 Countries And Territories Through A Network Of Approximately 600 Company-Owned And Independent Distributor Locations And Approximately 7,200 Dealer Locations. Cummins Earned $1.4 Billion On Sales Of $19.1 Billion IN 2015.

The Company S Techniques And Procedures Have Been Designed To Recover These Metals From Liquids, Solid Burnables, Multi Layered Digestables, And Pure Meltable Metals. The Company S Offices And Manufacturing Facilities Are Located IN Warwick, R.I.

Company Description: Bradford Soap Works Was Founded IN Rhode Island IN 1876. IN 1931 The Company Moved Into Its Present United States Headquarters IN West Warwick S Historic Valley Queen Mill. For Many Years The Company Focused Primarily On Soaps For The Textile Industry, But Since The Late 1940s It Has Steadily Broadened Its Product Line And Customer Base. Today, Bradford Ranks As One Of The World S Largest Independent Producers Of Specialty Bar Soaps And A Leading Supplier Of A Broad Range Of Personal Cleansing Products, Proprietary Soap Bases And Specialized Industrial Chemicals. Bradford Has Been Making Soap By The Traditional Full-Boiled Kettle Process For 125 Years. Today Modern Technology Guides The Process, But The Experience And Skills Of Its Soap Makers Are Still Critical To Achieving The Superior Results Kettle Processing Makes Possible. Bradford S Unique Kettle Soap Process Simulator, A Proprietary Computer-Modeling Program, Guides This Entire Process Under The Hands Of The Skilled Soap Maker.

Company Description: Dewolf Chemical, Inc Is A Marketer And Supplier Of Specialty Chemicals And Products To The Personal Care And Household, Industrial & Institutional Markets. Our Team Of Technical Account Executives Work With Our Customers To Assist With New Product Development And Source Next-Generation Technology. Partnerships With The Most Technically Competent Distributors Have Allowed US To Become An Industry Leader. Dewolf Chemical, Inc Markets To Both Mid-Atlantic And Northeastern States With Plans To Implement Future Expansion Into The Southeast And Midwest Regions. Dewolf Chemical, Inc Was Established IN 1942 Under The Name American Chemical & Solvent CO Initially, American Chemical Was A Supplier Of Chemical Processing Aids To The Wool And Textile Industries. As Industries IN The Northeast And Mid-Atlantic Changed From Textiles To A More Industrial Base, American Chemical Expanded Its Offering Of Specialty Chemicals IN Order To Serve Those New Markets. Today Under The Name Dewolf Chemical, Inc, Our Continued Focus Is To Supply The Highest Quality Performance-Based Specialty Chemicals To All The Markets We Serve. As A Company, We Continually Strive To Be An Integral Part Of The R&D Efforts Of Our Customers Which Are Enhanced By Our Unsurpassed Level Of Customer Service And Support. Dewolf Is Registered To The Iso 9001: 2000 Standard Along With Being Registered To The National Association Of Chemical Distributors Responsible Distribution Process . Our Business Policy: To Provide Quality Products And Service To Meet The Needs Of Our Customers. Our Business Goals And Objectives: * Our Primary Goal Is Customer Satisfaction. As Such, Each Member Of The Dewolf Chemical Team Is Responsibel For Ensuring That Internal And External Customer Requirements, Expectations And Needs Are Met. * Every Employee Is To Be Involved And Committed To Pursue The Principles Of Excellence. We Achieve This By Improving Processes, Methods, And Work Environment To Ensure Each Customer Is Receiving The Quality Product At Committed Cost, On Time. * To Represent Manufacturers Dedicated To The Development Of New Chemistries That Replace Hazardous And/OR Less Efficient Technology. * To Represent Manufacturers Committed To Producing The Highest Quality Products IN Their Respective Fields And To Reinvestment IN Their Process And People.

Company Description: Fujifilm Electronic Materials U.S.A. Designs And Manufactures A Variety Of Semiconductors And Related Products For Commercial And Industrial Clients Throughout The World. Its Products Are Used IN A Range Of Applications, Including Broadband, G-Line, E-Beam And Extreme Ultraviolet Technology. The Company Offers Engineering, Technical Support, And Research And Development Services. It Has Partnerships With The Massachusetts Institute Of Technology And The University Of Texas. Company Description: Organic Dyestuffs Corporation (Orco) Supplies Dyes, Pigments And Chemical Auxiliaries For Industrial Coloring Purposes. The Company Serves A Broad Base Of Customers IN Textile, Paper, Ink And Other Industries Where Color Applications Are Required. Orco Has Sales, Production, Warehouse And Laboratory Facilities IN Rhode Island, North Carolina And Georgia, As Well As A Sales Office And Warehouse Distribution Point IN Los Angeles. Orco DE Mexico Is The Distributor For Organic Dyestuffs Corporation IN Puebla, Mexico, Which Is Approximately One Hour South Of Mexico City. With Production Facilities And Warehouses Strategically Located Throughout The United States, Standard Products Are Typically Shipped Within 24 Hours. Orco S Continued Growth Is Based On Competitive High Quality Products Backed By Complete Customer Technical Services That Range From IN-House Laboratory Service And Customer IN-Plant Production Troubleshooting, To Quick Response Order Processing. Orco Was Established IN 1949, When Samuel Stott, John Sandilands And John Gormley Formed What Was Then Called Organic Chemical Corporation IN A Small Building On A Side Street IN Providence, R.I.

Additionally, The Company Provides Repair And Plant Maintenance, Training And Consulting Services. Baldor Dodge Reliance Is A Branch Of Baldor Electric, Its Parent Company. Balder Electric Manufactures Industrial Electric Motors, Controls And Drives That Power Products, Including Giant Rock Tumblers And Industrial Pumps.
